{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/WorkingInVsCode","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"title":"Working in VS Code","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/workinginvscode"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Developing with SwiftGodot","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/tutorials\/SwiftGodot-Tutorials","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/DebugInXcode"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Develop and debug SwfitGodot Code in Visual Studio Code","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual Studio Code provides a compelling alternative to Xcode for SwiftGodot"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"developers on Mac, Linux, or Windows.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"text":"Prerequisites","anchor":"Prerequisites","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To develop with SwiftGodot in Visual Studio Code, you will need the following"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"prerequisites:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Godot Engine without .NET support from the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/godotengine.org\/download\/"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual Studio Code from the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/code.visualstudio.com\/Download","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Install Swift from the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/install\/Swift","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"text":"Configuring Visual Studio Code","type":"heading","anchor":"Configuring-Visual-Studio-Code","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Swift Extension for Visual Studio Code from the Swift Server Work Group","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"provides code completion, code navigation, build task creation, and integration","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with LLDB for debugging, along with many other features for devloping code with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Install the Swift Extension for Visual Studio from the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/marketplace.visualstudio.com\/items?itemName=sswg.swift-lang"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or search for Swift on the Extensions tab in Visual Studio Code."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Installing the Swift Extension will automatically install the CodeLLDB Extension"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as a dependency for Visual Studio Code for debugging support."}]},{"text":"Create a Swift library package for your project","anchor":"Create-a-Swift-library-package-for-your-project","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create a folder on disk in a file location near the Godot project that you want","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to use with SwiftGodot.  For this article, we will assume you are working"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"against the sample project and code from the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/migueldeicaza.github.io\/SwiftGodotDocs\/tutorials\/swiftgodot-tutorials","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On the commmand line, change directories into the folder you created and run the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"swift package command to initialize a new library package:","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift package init --type library"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can now open your package folder in Visual Studio Code:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"code ."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Or use the “Open Folder…” File menu option in Visual Studio Code.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Setup-SwiftGodot-in-Packageswift","level":3,"text":"Setup SwiftGodot in Package.swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inside Visual Studio Code, open Package.swift"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set your library type to dynamic by adding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"type: .dynamic,"},{"type":"text","text":" to the products library section of your package configuration. E.g.,"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":[".library(","   name: \"SimpleRunnerDriver\",","   type: .dynamic,","   targets: [\"SimpleRunnerDriver\"]),"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add the SwiftGodot dependency to your package.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["dependencies: [","   .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/migueldeicaza\/SwiftGodot\", branch: \"main\")","],"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Modify your library target to reference the SwitGodot dependency, and add","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"necessary swift compiler and linker settings:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":[".target(","   name: \"SimpleRunnerDriver\",","   dependencies: [","         \"SwiftGodot\",","   ],","   swiftSettings: [.unsafeFlags([\"-suppress-warnings\"])]","),"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At this point, you should be able to follow the Meet SwiftGodot Tutorial"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"beginning in Section 2."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Building your SwiftGodot package","anchor":"Building-your-SwiftGodot-package"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you are ready to build your SwiftGodot package, the Swift Extension"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"provides a default Build task you can execute with Visual Studio Code’s Build"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Shortcut - Ctrl+Shift+B (or Cmd+Shift+B on Mac)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The initial build, especially on Windows, may take a very long time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Setting up your gdextension","type":"heading","anchor":"Setting-up-your-gdextension"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When creating your ","type":"text"},{"code":"gdextension","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" file, your configuration file will need to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"contain settings specific to your platform, and you will need to copy the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"libraries for your operating system and architecture to the ","type":"text"},{"code":"bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" folder inside","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"your Godot project."}]},{"text":"Windows","anchor":"Windows","type":"heading","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Windows does not deal well with long paths, so you should make sure that you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"either checkout your SwiftGodot into a toplevel directory, or use the Windows"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"subst"},{"text":" command to map a drive name to the location that contains your","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftGodot builds."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are developing on Windows, your "},{"code":"libraries","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dependencies"},{"text":" will need","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to be specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"windows.debug.x86_64"},{"text":" and your libraries will be compiled","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dll"},{"type":"text","text":" files, so that these sections should look like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["[libraries]","windows.debug.x86_64 = \"res:\/\/bin\/SimpleRunnerDriver.dll\"","","[dependencies]","windows.debug.x86_64 = {\"res:\/\/bin\/SwiftGodot.dll\" : \"\"}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can copy these files to your Godot projects "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"bin"},{"type":"text","text":" folder from the build"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"output folder located in "},{"code":".build\\x86_64-unknown-windows-msvc\\debug\\","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" inside"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the directory where you initialized your Swift package."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As an additional step on Windows, you will need to copy all of the Swift"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"runtime libraries into the ","type":"text"},{"code":"bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" folder with SwiftGodot.dll.  This is means"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"copying all "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"*.dll"},{"type":"text","text":" files from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C:\\Program Files\\Swift\\runtime-development\\usr\\bin\\"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Linux","anchor":"Linux","level":4},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are developing on Linux, your "},{"code":"libraries","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dependencies"},{"text":" will need","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to be specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"linux.debug.x86_64"},{"type":"text","text":" and your libraries will be compiled into"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lib*.so"},{"text":" files, so that these sections should look like this:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["[libraries]","linux.debug.x86_64 = \"res:\/\/bin\/libSimpleRunnerDriver.so\"","","[dependencies]","linux.debug.x86_64 = {\"res:\/\/bin\/libSwiftGodot.so\" : \"\"}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can copy these files to your Godot projects "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"bin"},{"type":"text","text":" folder from the build"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"output folder located in ","type":"text"},{"code":".build\/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\/debug\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" inside"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the directory where you initialized your Swift package.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Debugging your SwiftGodot code","anchor":"Debugging-your-SwiftGodot-code","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can debug your SwiftGodot code on Windows or Linux using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"CodeLLDB Extension to attach to your game launched from Godot."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In order to do this, you will need to add an Attach to Process"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"launch task  to your project.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In Visual Sutdio Code, switch to the “Run and Debug” tab.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a "},{"code":"launch.json","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" file by tapping on “create a launch.json file”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and selecting “LLDB”, which should be the first suggested option.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the newly created launch.json file, you should have a single","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lldb task.  To turn this task into an attach task:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Change the value for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"request"},{"type":"text","text":" from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launch"},{"type":"text","text":" to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"attach"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Change the value for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Attach to PID"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Remove the lines for ","type":"text"},{"code":"program","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"args"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"code":"cwd","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a line for "},{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with value ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"${command:pickProcess}"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Your launch configuration for lldb should now look like this:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["\"type\": \"lldb\",","\"request\": \"attach\",","\"name\": \"Attach to PID\",","\"pid\": \"${command:pickProcess}\""]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once you save this file, Attach to PID should be the default debug","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"task, and can be run by pressing F5.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To debug your app,","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, take note of running Godot process PIDs by running “Attach to PID”"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and searching for Godot."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Launch your game from Godot"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Return to Visual Studio and press F5 to run “Attach to PID” again."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Search again for Godot and select the PID for your game, which should be the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"only process that wasn’t listed in step (1) above.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Linux or Mac, it may be possible to differentiate your game’s PID from other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Godot PIDs by looking at the additional information Visual Studio Code lists about","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"each process, including command line options.  On Windows, the Godot processes are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"pretty much identical, making it difficult to differentiate your game from the editor.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At this point, Visual Studio Code should now stop on any breakpoints you have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"set, and you should be able to inspect Variables, set Watches, etc."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"warning","name":"Warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"On Mac, you will need to make your Godot engine debuggable following the steps from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this article "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/migueldeicaza.github.io\/SwiftGodotDocs\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/debuginxcode","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"references":{"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=sswg.swift-lang":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/marketplace.visualstudio.com\/items?itemName=sswg.swift-lang","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual Studio"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Marketplace","type":"text"}],"title":"Visual Studio Marketplace","url":"https:\/\/marketplace.visualstudio.com\/items?itemName=sswg.swift-lang"},"https://www.swift.org/install/Swift":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"official Swift website","type":"text"}],"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/install\/Swift","title":"official Swift website","identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/install\/Swift"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","title":"SwiftGodot","role":"collection","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"},"https://migueldeicaza.github.io/SwiftGodotDocs/documentation/swiftgodot/debuginxcode":{"identifier":"https:\/\/migueldeicaza.github.io\/SwiftGodotDocs\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/debuginxcode","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Debug in Xcode","type":"text"}],"title":"Debug in Xcode","url":"https:\/\/migueldeicaza.github.io\/SwiftGodotDocs\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/debuginxcode"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/DebugInXcode":{"title":"Debug in Xcode","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Debug Swift code written for Godot in Xcode.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/debuginxcode","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/DebugInXcode"},"https://migueldeicaza.github.io/SwiftGodotDocs/tutorials/swiftgodot-tutorials":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Meet SwiftGodot Tutorial","type":"text"}],"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/migueldeicaza.github.io\/SwiftGodotDocs\/tutorials\/swiftgodot-tutorials","title":"Meet SwiftGodot Tutorial","identifier":"https:\/\/migueldeicaza.github.io\/SwiftGodotDocs\/tutorials\/swiftgodot-tutorials"},"doc://SwiftGodot/tutorials/SwiftGodot-Tutorials":{"kind":"overview","url":"\/tutorials\/swiftgodot-tutorials","title":"Meet SwiftGodot","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftGodot allows developers to take new and existing Swift packages and use them as extensions for the Godot game engine."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/tutorials\/SwiftGodot-Tutorials","type":"topic","role":"overview"},"https://godotengine.org/download/":{"identifier":"https:\/\/godotengine.org\/download\/","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"official Godot website","type":"text"}],"title":"official Godot website","url":"https:\/\/godotengine.org\/download\/"},"https://code.visualstudio.com/Download":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"official Visual Studio Code website","type":"text"}],"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/code.visualstudio.com\/Download","title":"official Visual Studio Code website","identifier":"https:\/\/code.visualstudio.com\/Download"}}}